ncy impacts**\\n\\nI’m thinking about how adding a dependency might only affect the test project. It seems like I should consider implementing a user-code-filter to allow user packages for the agent. This might help streamline things and prevent unnecessary complications in the primary code. I want to ensure that I’m keeping user experience in mind while also making my codebase cleaner. There’s a lot to explore here, so I’ll keep working on it!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_b7BZ0QAzeHh5f0KLvWagwdMO|fc_0f1153feb7ac16c80169f55a9b9f2881a3a130bf5862fd1700", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/ant/ant/1.6/user-code-filter.json"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 268, "output": 1312, "cacheRead": 19968, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 21548, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777687172058, "responseId": "resp_0f1153feb7ac16c80169f55a84830081a386a8b80e6865df3c"}}
