’s crucial for the task.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating runtime class path in Gradle**\\n\\nI’m exploring how to set the `java.class.path` runtime in `build.gradle`. It seems like adding `runtimeArgs(\\\"-Djava.class.path=${sourceSets.test.runtimeClasspath.asPath}\\\")` is a potential solution, but there’s concern about native executables not being able to load classes from jars due to unsupported features. To address this, I think I need to add a second test that catches the `Error`, particularly for JVM agent compatibility. I’ll also need to check unsupported feature errors specifically and may consider using `ChainReaderHelper` for reflection instead.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring classpath setup with AntClassLoader**\\n\\nI’m considering using `AntClassLoader` because `ChainReaderHelper` doesn’t expose necessary details. I need to find the classpath path in my Java test. First, I plan to create a `Project` object, then set up a `Path` using `System.getProperty(\\\"java.class.path\\\")`, which could include class directories and jars. For constructing the `AntClassLoader`, I’m debating whether to set the parent to the system class loader or leave it as null. This setup seems promising for what I need!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_NmgIJeUpe6msgqIhoTJEigPz|fc_0f1153feb7ac16c80169f55c78382c81a3a28780aca985905b", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge10/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/ant/ant/1.6/main/extracted/main/org/apache/tools/ant/AntClassLoader.java", "offset": 280, "limit": 80}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1768, "output": 3177, "cacheRead": 37376, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 42321, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777687623998, "responseId": "resp_0f1153feb7ac16c80169f55c48933081a39cf06e3e